data.description: **Preferred lender is offering a $2,000 lender credit toward interest rate buy-down or closing costs** Step inside this 4-bed, 2.5-bath home and be greeted by a spacious and open floor plan lined with windows offering tons of natural light. The kitchen is a chef's delight, featuringgranite countertops, stainless appliances, a huge island that allows for additional seating, and a deep pantry. It seamlessly flows into the dining area, which offers a view of the privatebackyard. The airy living room is perfect for hosting family and friends comfortably. Upstairs is the over-sized master bedroom and ensuite bath featuring a stand-alone shower, dual vanities and huge walk-in closet. Three additional bedrooms upstairs share a guest bath with dual vanities and a shower/tub combo. The laundry room is also conveniently located on the second floor. Washer and dryer included! The home features aa 20 x 20 two-car garage with storage shelves. A spacious backyard deck provides the perfect spot for grilling out with family and friends. The yard is an ideal space for kids to play, featuring a playground and a trampoline that convey with the home. Enjoy easy access to the Bay and nearby parks for the kids. The family-friendly neighborhood offers a sense of community and safety for children to grow and play. Less than a ten-minute drive and you'll be at one of the many beach accesses. This home is not just a house; it's a haven for family life offering comfort, convenience, and the opportunity to create cherished memories.
